@analytic-memory text
Use analytic-memory for structured accumulation, rollups, derived metrics, and exportable summaries that span many observations.
Prefer it when the task is about storing keyed facts, appending evidence, computing aggregates, or exporting a compact session-level summary for later steps.
It is best for inspectable session memory and evidence ledgers, not for one-off narrative explanations.
Do not use it for open-ended prose generation, arbitrary scripting, or KB retrieval.
Good bodies look like normalized operator instructions such as store, append, derive, rollup, and export.
